trend_summary: Across the image sequence, tree-covered lots give way to new subdivisions, retail roofs, and wider arterial roads. Built space expands gradually but greenspace corridors persist, keeping an overall leafy suburban character. Growth concentrates along the north–south highway and near junctions, indicating car-oriented infill rather than high-rise intensification.
notable_changes: Progressive clearing of forest patches in the north-central zone for residential blocks.
Construction and later widening of the main north–south highway; new cloverleaf added in the northeast.
Emergence of large, light-colored commercial/warehouse roofs in the southern sector.
Steady residential infill inside earlier street grids, reducing vacant lots.
New sports fields and pocket parks created to compensate for lost greenery.
